thread.title: LSU, Alabama, Florida, Ole Miss win big in Week 6
thread.title_full: LSU, Alabama, Florida, Ole Miss win big in Week 6 | NOLA.com

author: Jerit Roser, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: LSU, Alabama, Florida, Ole Miss win big in Week 6
text:
Ranked SEC teams LSU, Alabama, Florida and Ole Miss won their four contests Saturday by a combined 145-44.
The No. 7 Tigers (5-0, 3-0) took care of South Carolina (2-4, 0-4), 45-24.
The No. 8 Crimson Tide (5-1, 2-1) actually survived the closest call of that group against Arkansas (2-4, 1-2) â€” trailing 7-3 into the second half before scoring 24 straight points in an eventual 27-14 victory.
The No. 11 Gators (6-0, 4-0) cruised through a 21-3 defeat of Missouri (4-2, 1-2), and the No. 14 Rebels (5-1, 2-1) rolled past New Mexico State, 52-3.
No. 19 Georgia (4-2, 2-2) was the league's only ranked team to falter, losing to SEC East rival Tennessee (3-3, 1-2), 38-31, after losing star running back Nick Chubb to a leg injury early in the contest.
CHECK OUT THE UPDATED SEC STANDINGS LSU, Florida and No. 9 Texas A&M (5-0, 2-0), who enjoyed a bye this week, remained undefeated for one more week.
But at least one of those is guaranteed to suffer its first defeat next Saturday as the Gators visit the Tigers, while the Aggies have no cakewalk of an Oct. 17 matchup, either, with Alabama coming to town.
Behind that group, the SEC's only remaining one-loss team, either than Alabama or Ole Miss?
Kentucky, at 4-1 and 2-1 in league play.
